  "description": "Longest-contiguous-match core of CPython's difflib.SequenceMatcher (autojunk=False, isjunk=None): findLongestMatch/getMatchingBlocks/matchSize with witness-maximality-tie-break specs anchored on a frozen common-block notion (isCommonBlock, stated with List.drop/List.take). findLongestMatch returns the UNIQUE canonical longest common contiguous block (i,j,k) under the total order k maximal -> i minimal -> j minimal: the returned block is a genuine common run (witness), no common run is longer (maximality, load-bearing), and it is the canonically least such maximal block (i-min then j-min tie-break) -> unique. Witness alone is gamed by (0,0,0), so maximality and the tie-break are mandatory. getMatchingBlocks is specified by STRUCTURAL invariants anchored to findLongestMatch (every emitted block is a genuine common block, each block size <= the global longest match, monotone, sentinel (|a|,|b|,0) terminator, never empty), NOT against a reference diff. Deliberate scope: ONLY the per-call find_longest_match property + get_matching_blocks structural invariants are specified; the OVERALL Ratcliff-Obershelp diff is GREEDY, NOT a global optimum, so no spec claims global minimality of the block decomposition (that would be unsound). matchSize is a derived observer (third component of findLongestMatch). ratio/quick_ratio are excluded (Float). Sequences are List Nat.",
